# Same Tree

## Problem

Given the roots of two binary trees `p` and `q`, check whether they are the same.

Two trees are considered the same if:

* They have the same structure
* Corresponding nodes have the same values

---

## Concept

This problem is based on **recursion**.

We compare both trees node by node:

* Check current nodes
* Then recursively check left subtrees
* Then recursively check right subtrees

---

## Approach

* If both nodes are null → return true
* If one is null and other is not → return false
* If values are different → return false
* Otherwise:

  * Check left subtree
  * Check right subtree
* Return true only if both sides match

---

## Code (Java)

```java
class Solution {
    public boolean isSameTree(TreeNode p, TreeNode q) {
        if(p == null && q == null)
        {
            return true;
        }
        else if(p == null || q == null)
        {
            return false;
        }
        else if(p.val != q.val)
        {
            return false;
        }

        return isSameTree(p.left,q.left) && isSameTree(p.right,q.right);
    }
}
```

---

## Time Complexity

* O(n) → we compare every node once

## Space Complexity

* O(h) → recursion stack (h = height of tree)

---

## Mistakes / Learnings

* Don’t forget to handle null cases properly
* Both structure and values must match (not just values)
* Always check current node before going deeper
